Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the 
pasta.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 1cm 
chunks. Heat a large #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the pepper chunks and cook until charred, ~{5-6%minutes}. Adjust 
the heat if necessary. Stir only twice during this time - you want the 
pepper to pick up some nice colour.

Once charred, remove from the pan and set aside for later.

While the pepper chars, add the @linguine{180%g} to your pan of boiling water 
and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with 
@olive oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Put the large frying pan back on medium heat with a drizzle of @olive oil{} 
(no need to clean).

Once the oil is hot, add the @diced chorizo{120%g} and @sliced mushrooms{120%g}. 
Fry until golden, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}, then stir in the @tomato 
passata{1%carton}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}, 
@sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{50%ml} (see pantry for both amounts).

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Bring to the boil and simmer 
until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once the sauce has thickened, combine the charred pepper, cooked pasta and 
sauce in whichever pan is the largest.

Stir in half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}, adding a splash of 
@water{} if it's a little too thick.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if needed.

Share your mushroom and chorizo linguine between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle with the remaining cheese to finish. Enjoy!